14:02.108 --> 14:05.066
And this is me talking.

14:05.067 --> 14:08.441
- You gave the Scarecrow a heart.
- A calloused country guy here.

14:08.442 --> 14:10.066
- The Tin Man.
- For the first time in my life...

14:10.067 --> 14:11.774
Or Tin Man.

14:11.775 --> 14:13.357
Or I'm the Scarecrow,
and I don't have a brain.

14:13.358 --> 14:15.399
You gave the Tin Man a heart.
I'm sorry. Continue.

14:19.525 --> 14:22.065
- You see what you do to us?
- I'm sorry.

14:22.090 --> 14:23.941
- We're... We're falling over ourselves.
- What just happened?

14:23.942 --> 14:26.441
Literally, for
the first time in my life,

14:26.442 --> 14:29.274
I pictured myself,
while you were singing,

14:29.275 --> 14:33.066
me riding a unicorn,
the kind that has, like, wings.

14:33.067 --> 14:34.982
That's the vibe I was trying to get.

14:35.007 --> 14:36.044
- And I was holding a Care Bear,
- Wow.

14:36.068 --> 14:37.274
had a Care Bear right here.

14:37.299 --> 14:40.965
It was like... Your voice is like,
"What is happening to me?

14:40.989 --> 14:42.170
- Blake.
- Where am I?"

14:42.171 --> 14:43.982
- Like, you did that to me, Jaclyn.
- You made a grown man do that.

14:43.983 --> 14:46.941
It's amazing how one man's dream
is another man's nightmare.

14:48.942 --> 14:51.149
And even though there's
vocalists in this competition

14:51.150 --> 14:53.274
that literally blow the roof off
this place,

14:53.275 --> 14:55.482
I think what you do
is more powerful than that.

14:55.483 --> 14:57.982
- Thank you.
- I've got to have you on my team.

14:57.983 --> 15:00.232
- Please, Jaclyn. I love you.
- Let me take over...

15:00.233 --> 15:03.566
...before you say
any other strange things.

15:03.567 --> 15:05.899
I'm pretty sure that unicorn comment

15:05.900 --> 15:07.566
- disqualified him immediately.
- Just being honest. I'm just being honest.

15:07.567 --> 15:12.149
Jaclyn, you know, I'm also a
huge lover of the classic songs.

15:12.150 --> 15:15.857
I really get it, and I see exactly
what we could do together.

15:15.858 --> 15:18.357
We'd be able to find songs
that suit your voice,

15:18.358 --> 15:19.982
just like this one did,

15:19.983 --> 15:21.691
and we'll keep it pure.
We'll keep it honest.

15:21.692 --> 15:24.316
We'll keep it genuine,
and it'll be all about you.

15:24.317 --> 15:27.524
So, I really would love
to do that with you.

15:27.525 --> 15:32.191
All right, I think it's time
for you to pick a coach.

15:32.192 --> 15:36.607
It's either Alicia Keys,
goddess of all things wonderful,

15:36.608 --> 15:40.024
or it's, uh, you know, the
unicorn whisperer over there.

15:44.692 --> 15:47.324
I would love to work with
either one of you, honestly.

15:51.207 --> 15:53.316
Um, but I pick...

15:57.233 --> 15:59.566
- ...Alicia.
- All right!

15:59.567 --> 16:01.691
Come on!

16:01.692 --> 16:03.357
I'm having a rough start right now,

16:03.358 --> 16:05.066
but I'm gonna make a comeback.

16:05.067 --> 16:06.422
- Congratulations to you.
- I'm sorry.

16:06.447 --> 16:10.501
Now I know that sharing what
goes on in my mind all the time

16:11.041 --> 16:13.092
probably isn't the thing to do.

16:19.544 --> 16:21.171
