♪ I said, what a ma-a-a-n ♪

18:04.170 --> 18:05.877
♪ He's a good man ♪

18:05.878 --> 18:10.252
♪ A good, good ma-a-a-n ♪

18:10.253 --> 18:12.419
♪ What a man, what a man, what a man ♪

18:12.420 --> 18:16.919
♪ What a mighty good, good, gooood man ♪

18:18.378 --> 18:20.086
Wow.

18:22.420 --> 18:26.752
- Aw! Aw!
- So close!

18:26.753 --> 18:29.169
- What is your name?
- My name's Sophia Dion.

18:29.170 --> 18:32.252
I'm 17 years old,
and I'm from Park City, Utah.

18:32.253 --> 18:34.647
Cool. And then are you...
Do you write music, as well?

18:34.672 --> 18:36.163
I do. I write a lot of music.

18:36.188 --> 18:37.919
I like the soul/country kind of stuff.

18:37.920 --> 18:39.252
- Yes!
- Yeah.

18:39.253 --> 18:40.919
I was so close.

18:40.920 --> 18:43.252
I didn't even recognize the song
at first, did you?

18:43.253 --> 18:44.294
- No. Right, right.
- And then I was like, "Oh,

18:44.295 --> 18:46.294
♪ Yes, he is ♪

18:46.295 --> 18:49.031
Yeah, that was such a cool, like,
different arrangement.

18:49.056 --> 18:51.793
- Thank you.
- I was just waiting for a little extra,

18:51.795 --> 18:53.364
and that was the only reason
why didn't pick you.

18:53.389 --> 18:54.347
Thank you.

18:54.372 --> 18:57.252
If I can't understand what people
are saying when they're singing,

18:57.253 --> 18:58.877
it drives me nuts.

18:58.878 --> 19:00.127
And for the most part,
I could understand you,

19:00.128 --> 19:01.377
but there was a little bit of trying

19:01.378 --> 19:02.919
to decipher what the words were,

19:02.920 --> 19:04.419
and maybe it was this new arrangement.

19:04.420 --> 19:06.294
It could have been cleaned up
just a little bit.

19:06.295 --> 19:09.127
- That's why I didn't hit my button.
- Thank you.

19:11.720 --> 19:13.536
- Do not take it too much to heart.
- Thank you.

19:15.295 --> 19:17.252
I'm so grateful
to be able to sing for you.

19:17.253 --> 19:20.086
Oh, no, and, baby girl.
You're 17. That's young.

19:20.087 --> 19:21.794
<i>As the auditions continued,</i>

19:21.795 --> 19:24.336
<i>Blake and Kelly both
had something specific in mind</i>

19:24.337 --> 19:26.961
<i>in their search for their
first artists of the night,</i>

19:26.962 --> 19:29.002
<i>and these singers just missed the mark.</i>

19:29.003 --> 19:31.586
♪ If you trust your rebel heart ♪

19:31.587 --> 19:33.919
♪ Ride it into battle ♪

19:33.920 --> 19:35.586
♪ Don't be afraid ♪

19:35.587 --> 19:38.169
