19:45.462 --> 19:47.502
So, that was the only reason
why I didn't turn my chair.

19:47.503 --> 19:50.502
♪ Blue-ue-ue-ue ♪

19:50.503 --> 19:54.252
♪ Looks good on the sky ♪

19:54.253 --> 19:56.461
There was one moment where
the song got away from you.

19:56.462 --> 19:59.336
You went for something big.
It didn't land correctly.

19:59.337 --> 20:03.586
♪ We were legends ♪

20:05.337 --> 20:07.627
I just don't know that
that was the best song

20:07.628 --> 20:09.502
to showcase what you are capable of.

20:09.503 --> 20:11.127
If you could have put together

20:11.128 --> 20:15.044
a more start-to-finish, solid audition,

20:15.045 --> 20:17.502
we'd be sitting here fighting
over you right now, you know,

20:17.503 --> 20:20.044
because I think you have
the talent to be on this show.

20:20.045 --> 20:23.044
- Thank you so much.
- That was tricky. I was close.

20:23.045 --> 20:25.711
It is so hard watching
good people go home,

20:25.712 --> 20:28.337
but I'm looking for something
that really moves me.

20:34.557 --> 20:35.883
♪ This is "The Voice" ♪

20:35.922 --> 20:37.708
<i>Welcome back to the blind auditions</i>

20:37.748 --> 20:39.502
<i>at Universal Studios Hollywood.</i>

20:39.503 --> 20:44.377
T-e-a-m K-e-l-l-y.

20:44.378 --> 20:45.961
Winner!

20:47.503 --> 20:49.711
I hope it's country,
and I hope I get her.

20:49.712 --> 20:51.419
- "Her"?
- I don't know.

20:51.420 --> 20:53.044
I'm just putting it out there.

20:53.045 --> 20:54.544
<i>Let's see if this next artist,</i>

20:54.545 --> 20:56.211
<i>34-year-old Molly Stevens,</i>

20:56.212 --> 20:58.336
<i>is the one Kelly has been waiting for.</i>

20:58.337 --> 21:00.211
The genre that I think I'd put myself in

21:00.212 --> 21:02.211
is probably country,

21:02.212 --> 21:05.044
but I've gotten more
into the Americana realm.

21:05.045 --> 21:08.377
I think they both share
beautiful storytelling.

21:08.378 --> 21:10.377
I grew up in Macon, Georgia.

21:10.378 --> 21:12.544
My grandfather was a Baptist preacher.

21:12.545 --> 21:15.586
He had a TV show that aired
every single Christmas

21:15.587 --> 21:17.377
through the middle Georgia area.

21:17.378 --> 21:20.544
That's where I probably got
my first start singing.

21:20.545 --> 21:23.502
I knew that I was gay
when I was a very young kid.

21:23.503 --> 21:26.377
Being a Southern Baptist,
I thought that was a big sin

21:26.378 --> 21:28.044
and I was gonna go to hell for it.

21:28.045 --> 21:30.294
Coming out to my parents was tough.

21:30.295 --> 21:33.377
I don't think they knew how to take it.

21:33.378 --> 21:36.419
Even though my parents
haven't always seen eye to eye,

21:36.420 --> 21:38.294
we've come a really long way,

21:38.295 --> 21:41.211
and I'm so happy
they're here with me today.

21:41.212 --> 21:43.377
I moved to Nashville in 2010,

21:43.378 --> 21:46.044
and I started making music
and playing shows

21:46.045 --> 21:47.711
all around the Southeast.

21:47.712 --> 21:50.086
- How's it going? It's a grind, right?
- It is a grind, yes.

21:50.087 --> 21:52.294
I'm trying to get my break,
honestly, Carson.

21:52.295 --> 21:54.681
You're here. You got your break.

21:56.295 --> 21:58.627
I met Ashlee, my fiancée,

21:58.628 --> 22:01.212
about three years ago
in Raleigh, North Carolina.

22:01.237 --> 22:02.544
We both come from

22:02.545 --> 22:06.127
Southern Baptist family and
background, and we connected.

22:06.128 --> 22:08.794
It's so great to be here today,
and I'm so proud of Molly.

22:08.795 --> 22:10.294
I think she's worked really hard.

22:10.295 --> 22:12.127
And she's my best friend,

22:12.128 --> 22:15.169
and I am incredibly grateful
to have her by my side.

22:15.170 --> 22:17.502
Ashlee is a wonderful woman.

22:17.503 --> 22:19.794
We love her like another daughter.

22:19.795 --> 22:22.586
And I am so proud of Molly.

22:22.587 --> 22:25.461
She's finally getting some recognition

22:25.462 --> 22:28.336
that she very much deserves.

22:30.170 --> 22:33.127
My entire life, every adversity
that I've gone through,

22:33.128 --> 22:35.502
I've always come out stronger for it.

22:35.503 --> 22:37.252
And I believe that, today,

22:37.253 --> 22:39.795
I'm gonna come out stronger
because I'm a fighter.

