Whoo!

24:26.753 --> 24:29.086
- Yes!
- Yeah! Yeah!

24:29.087 --> 24:33.044
- Way to go!
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!

24:35.628 --> 24:37.961
Yeah!

24:37.962 --> 24:40.377
- Yeah!
- Oh, gosh, whatever.

24:40.378 --> 24:42.544
Whew! What's your name?

24:42.545 --> 24:44.919
Molly Stevens from Macon, Georgia,

24:44.920 --> 24:46.752
and I live in Raleigh,
North Carolina, now.

24:46.753 --> 24:48.627
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

24:48.628 --> 24:50.461
You know anything about North Carolina?

24:50.462 --> 24:52.294
My family's here.
They're from North Carolina.

24:52.295 --> 24:53.919
All right! Way to go.

24:53.920 --> 24:56.419
- Do you know who sang that song?
- Molly. Molly just sang it.

24:56.420 --> 24:57.505
- No, you don't!
- Yes!

24:57.529 --> 24:58.668
I know who sang that song.

24:58.670 --> 25:00.002
That's one of my favorite
singer/songwriters.

25:00.003 --> 25:02.086
- Sweet. Me too. Yes!
- Patty Griffin, girl.

25:02.087 --> 25:04.836
- Do you want to do soulful country/rock?
- Yeah, country, Americana.

25:04.837 --> 25:06.086
- Come on.
- Yeah.

25:06.087 --> 25:07.502
Oh, gosh.

25:07.503 --> 25:08.961
Okay, well, I've won country awards,

25:08.962 --> 25:10.586
and I, you know... Patty Griffin...

25:10.587 --> 25:12.419
Why are you selling yourself
to me? Talk to her.

25:12.420 --> 25:14.419
People only believe,
if you're country on this show,

25:14.420 --> 25:16.627
that Blake can help you,
but that is not true.

25:16.628 --> 25:18.461
I have had no help from Blake,

25:18.462 --> 25:20.269
and I have been successful
in country music.

25:20.294 --> 25:24.752
I'm just saying. Thank you. Thank you.

25:24.753 --> 25:26.499
My life is country music.

25:26.524 --> 25:28.857
I don't go from one genre to the next.

25:28.882 --> 25:30.961
- I stay in one lane.
- You know what?

25:30.986 --> 25:33.351
I am country and I'm proud
of it, and that's all I do!

25:33.376 --> 25:36.002
- I can't help it. I can't help it.
- That's all I do!

25:36.003 --> 25:38.002
- All right, wait.
- And I'm serious about it!

25:38.003 --> 25:40.669
- Okay, Blake. Okay, hold on.
- I'm serious!

25:43.212 --> 25:46.461
I cannot help
that I love all genres of music.

25:46.462 --> 25:50.461
Who here has one genre of music on
your iPhone that you listen to?

25:50.462 --> 25:51.836
- No one.
- I do.

25:51.837 --> 25:53.711
You are a damn liar.
I've seen your iPhone.

25:53.712 --> 25:55.627
- I'm country. I'm damn country.
- You love Duran Duran.

25:55.628 --> 25:57.544
I have the "Ghostbusters II" soundtrack,

25:57.545 --> 25:59.211
- and that's the only other...
- You are a liar!

25:59.212 --> 26:00.669
- ...music that I have.
- He is a liar.

26:00.670 --> 26:03.169
Do you want a liar for a coach?
I'm truthful.

26:03.170 --> 26:05.759
Molly, I'm not gonna lie.
I think Kelly is a good fit for you.

26:05.784 --> 26:07.794
- Yeah? Yeah? Yeah?
- Thank you, Adam.

26:07.795 --> 26:11.002
I bet that's shocking to hear.

26:11.003 --> 26:13.669
- I will say, strategically on the show...
- Yeah?

26:13.670 --> 26:16.502
...your chances are higher with Kelly.

26:16.503 --> 26:20.002
But I like Blake, as well.

26:20.003 --> 26:23.086
No matter what they say,
it's fun to watch you perform

26:23.087 --> 26:24.902
because it just looks like you're just

26:24.926 --> 26:27.505
- sinking your teeth into this song.
- Absolutely.

26:27.545 --> 26:30.719
And I don't know if that was you
playing the arpeggio part on the...

26:30.744 --> 26:32.919
- Oh, Lord.
- ...on the acoustic, but I...

26:32.920 --> 26:35.086
He's so smart with his musical terms.

26:35.087 --> 26:37.044
He Googled that term
like five minutes ago.

26:37.045 --> 26:38.629
- You see what's happening here, Molly?
- I see that.

26:38.654 --> 26:40.187
It doesn't matter what I say.

26:42.003 --> 26:43.669
You're not confined to one thing.

26:43.670 --> 26:45.252
You don't sound like
every other country artist.

26:45.253 --> 26:46.877
I think that's why Chris Stapleton

26:46.878 --> 26:48.711
- sounds so great in this genre.
- Yeah.

26:48.712 --> 26:50.044
Kacey Musgraves is stepping out,

26:50.045 --> 26:52.919
doing something different,
and that is captivating.

26:52.920 --> 26:55.211
- Yes, Kelly.
- And that is why, ma'am,

26:55.212 --> 26:57.586
- you should be on my team.
- Yes!

26:59.087 --> 27:02.318
Hey, Molly, who do you pick
as your coach?

27:02.343 --> 27:04.627
Oh, man.

27:07.573 --> 27:09.160
- Who's she gonna pick?
- I say Blake.

27:09.185 --> 27:12.309
- Kelly.
- I think Blake.

27:12.753 --> 27:14.127
Come on, Molly!

27:23.253 --> 27:25.294
- I pick Kelly!
- Yeah!

27:25.295 --> 27:28.627
Yes!

27:28.628 --> 27:31.127
Yes!

27:31.128 --> 27:32.087
Yeah!

27:32.088 --> 27:33.752
Sorry, Blake.

27:33.753 --> 27:36.294
Yes! Oh, my gosh.

27:36.295 --> 27:38.044
I'm so excited about Molly.

27:38.045 --> 27:40.127
I think that we connect on the soulful,

27:40.128 --> 27:42.377
like, rock, like, country.
Like, I love all those things.

27:42.378 --> 27:44.961
- Yes!
- I can't help you now, Molly.

27:44.962 --> 27:47.086
I can't help you now.

27:47.087 --> 27:50.752
It's easy to see that the
other three coaches gang up on me.

27:50.753 --> 27:54.086
I mean, it takes three of them
to go against one of me.

27:54.087 --> 27:56.562
Hey! Hey!

27:56.587 --> 27:59.554
I have no one on my team yet today,

27:59.579 --> 28:01.689
and I'm starting to feel
a little bit left out.

28:07.462 --> 28:09.461
That was a team effort.

28:09.462 --> 28:13.169
Did that feel good?
'Cause it felt good here.

28:13.170 --> 28:15.169
